blishing a generic agent runtime script with main and subagent loops using JSON files. I’ll consider using Node ES modules directly.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Planning agent system setup**\\n\\nI need to use child_process spawn. I’m thinking of creating several files within an agent-system directory, like a README.md, filePipeline.mjs, and others to organize the structure. Since the user wants a proper setup, I should ensure to create the actual directories and files. Each worktree will need its own config, logs, task queues, and maybe some feedback mechanisms.\\n\\nI’m also considering how the main agent will handle outputs and route tasks efficiently, ensuring that subagents remain independent without direct communication. I'll write scripts outside of the app, utilizing Node standard libraries.\"}]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_k5TCsQiR3MDM9zKOr0PjBaqu|fc_0b22d22025c20ba70169e9fd2f3098819185216721d176d082","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/agent-system/lib/filePipeline.mjs","content":"import fs from 'node:fs/promises';\nimport path from 'node:path';\n\nexport async function ensureDir(dirPath) {\n  await fs.mkdir(dirPath, { recursive: true });\n}\n\nexport async function ensureJsonFile(filePath, defaultValue) {\n  await ensureDir(path.dirname(filePath));\n  try {\n    await fs.access(filePath);\n  } catch {\n    await fs.writeFile(filePath, JSON.stringify(defaultValue, null, 2));\n  }\n}\n\nexport async function readJson(filePath, fallback) {\n  try {\n    const raw = await fs.readFile(filePath, 'utf8');\n    return JSON.parse(raw);\n  } catch {\n    return fallback;\n  }\n}\n\nexport async function writeJson(filePath, value) {\n  await ensureDir(path.dirname(filePath));\n  await fs.writeFile(filePath, JSON.stringify(value, null, 2));\n}\n\nexport async function appendLog(filePath, message) {\n  await ensureDir(path.dirname(filePath));\n  const line = `[${new Date().toISOString()}] ${message}\\n`;\n  await fs.appendFile(filePath, line);\n}\n\nexport async function updateMarkdownSection(filePath, heading, content) {\n  let text = '';\n  try {\n    text = await fs.readFile(filePath, 'utf8');\n  } catch {\n    text = '';\n  }\n\n  const normalized = text.trim().length > 0 ? `${text.trimEnd()}\\n` : '';\n  const section = `## ${heading}\\n${content.trim()}\\n`;\n  const pattern = new RegExp(`## ${heading}[\\\\s\\\\S]*?(?=\\\\n## |$)`, 'm');\n  const next = pattern.test(normalized)\n    ? normalized.replace(pattern, section)\n    : `${normalized}${normalized ? '\\n' : ''}${section}`;\n\n  await fs.writeFile(filePath, `${next.trimEnd()}\\n`);\n}\n\nexport async function appendMarkdown(filePath, content) {\n  await ensureDir(path.dirname(filePath));\n  await fs.appendFile(filePath, `${content.trim()}\\n\\n`);\n}\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/agent-system/lib/filePipeline.mjs\",\"content\":\"import fs from 'node:fs/promises';\\nimport path from 'node:path';\\n\\nexport async function ensureDir(dirPath) {\\n  await fs.mkdir(dirPath, { recursive: true });\\n}\\n\\nexport async function ensureJsonFile(filePath, defaultValue) {\\n  await ensureDir(path.dirname(filePath));\\n  try {\\n    await fs.access(filePath);\\n  } catch {\\n    await fs.writeFile(filePath, JSON.stringify(defaultValue, null, 2));\\n  }\\n}\\n\\nexport async function readJson(filePath, fallback) {\\n  try {\\n    const raw = await fs.readFile(filePath, 'utf8');\\n    return JSON.parse(raw);\\n  } catch {\\n    return fallback;\\n  }\\n}\\n\\nexport async function writeJson(filePath, value) {\\n  await ensureDir(path.dirname(filePath));\\n  await fs.writeFile(filePath, JSON.stringify(value, null, 2));\\n}\\n\\nexport async function appendLog(filePath, message) {\\n  await ensureDir(path.dirname(filePath));\\n  const line = `[${new Date().toISOString()}] ${message}\\\\n`;\\n  await fs.appendFile(filePath, line);\\n}\\n\\nexport async function updateMarkdownSection(filePath, heading, content) {\\n  let text = '';\\n  try {\\n    text = await fs.readFile(filePath, 'utf8');\\n  } catch {\\n    text = '';\\n  }\\n\\n  const normalized = text.trim().length > 0 ? `${text.trimEnd()}\\\\n` : '';\\n  const section = `## ${heading}\\\\n${content.trim()}\\\\n`;\\n  const pattern = new RegExp(`## ${heading}[\\\\\\\\s\\\\\\\\S]*?(?=\\\\\\\\n## |$)`, 'm');\\n  const next = pattern.test(normalized)\\n    ? normalized.replace(pattern, section)\\n    : `${normalized}${normalized ? '\\\\n' : ''}${section}`;\\n\\n  await fs.writeFile(filePath, `${next.trimEnd()}\\\\n`);\\n}\\n\\nexport async function appendMarkdown(filePath, content) {\\n  await ensureDir(path.dirname(filePath));\\n  await fs.appendFile(filePath, `${content.trim()}\\\\n\\\\n`);\\n}\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":638,"output":991,"cacheRead":15488,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":17117,"cost":{"input":0.001595,"output":0.014865,"cacheRead":0.003872,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.020332}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776942357782,"responseId":"resp_0b22d22025c20ba70169e9fd16000c8191a08d3effc7bff5ed"}}
