{"type":"message","id":"de3901fb","parentId":"29fa4ceb","timestamp":"2026-04-23T11:10:14.817Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_xrwOo1J42HlDIBNJMz9awBYx|fc_0b22d22025c20ba70169e9fe00b3cc8191b7faa62427432c25","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/agent-system/README.md","content":"# Agent System\n\nThis setup provisions two isolated git worktree subagents and a main coordinator.\n\n## Layout\n\n- Main repo: `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace`\n- Subagent worktrees:\n  - `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/agents/subagent-1` on `subagent-1-branch`\n  - `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/agents/subagent-2` on `subagent-2-branch`\n- Shared pipeline files:\n  - `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/pipeline/main_to_subagent_1.json`\n  - `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/pipeline/main_to_subagent_2.json`\n  - `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/pipeline/subagent_1_to_main.json`\n  - `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/pipeline/subagent_2_to_main.json`\n\n## Per-subagent assets\n\nEach subagent has:\n\n- `config.json`\n- `logs/`\n- `task-queue.json`\n- `vault/goals.md`\n- `vault/tasks.md`\n- `vault/memory.md`\n\n## Runtime behavior\n\n- `main-agent.mjs` seeds tasks, monitors outbound updates, evaluates results, and writes feedback into each subagent's `vault/memory.md`.\n- `subagent.mjs` runs an isolated read -> process -> write -> sleep loop against its own queue and pipeline files.\n- Subagents never read each other's files.\n\n## Start\n\n```bash\nbash /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/agent-system/start-all.sh\n```\n\n## Extending\n\n- Add more subagents by expanding `AGENTS` in `bootstrap.mjs` and `main-agent.mjs`.\n- Swap `evaluateTask()` in `subagent.mjs` with domain-specific executors.\n- Replace file polling with sockets or queues later without changing the agent contract.\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/agent-system/README.md\",\"content\":\"# Agent System\\n\\nThis setup provisions two isolated git worktree subagents and a main coordinator.\\n\\n## Layout\\n\\n- Main repo: `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace`\\n- Subagent worktrees:\\n  - `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/agents/subagent-1` on `subagent-1-branch`\\n  - `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/agents/subagent-2` on `subagent-2-branch`\\n- Shared pipeline files:\\n  - `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/pipeline/main_to_subagent_1.json`\\n  - `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/pipeline/main_to_subagent_2.json`\\n  - `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/pipeline/subagent_1_to_main.json`\\n  - `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/pipeline/subagent_2_to_main.json`\\n\\n## Per-subagent assets\\n\\nEach subagent has:\\n\\n- `config.json`\\n- `logs/`\\n- `task-queue.json`\\n- `vault/goals.md`\\n- `vault/tasks.md`\\n- `vault/memory.md`\\n\\n## Runtime behavior\\n\\n- `main-agent.mjs` seeds tasks, monitors outbound updates, evaluates results, and writes feedback into each subagent's `vault/memory.md`.\\n- `subagent.mjs` runs an isolated read -> process -> write -> sleep loop against its own queue and pipeline files.\\n- Subagents never read each other's files.\\n\\n## Start\\n\\n```bash\\nbash /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/agent-system/start-all.sh\\n```\\n\\n## Extending\\n\\n- Add more subagents by expanding `AGENTS` in `bootstrap.mjs` and `main-agent.mjs`.\\n- Swap `evaluateTask()` in `subagent.mjs` with domain-specific executors.\\n- Replace file polling with sockets or queues later without changing the agent contract.\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":211,"output":467,"cacheRead":20736,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":21414,"cost":{"input":0.0005275000000000001,"output":0.007005,"cacheRead":0.005183999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.012716499999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776942591087,"responseId":"resp_0b22d22025c20ba70169e9fdff580c8191941dd00d3cc6f21d"}}
