{"type":"message","id":"818f938f","parentId":"91ceeb13","timestamp":"2026-04-23T11:11:36.271Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Considering git worktree management**\n\nI’m thinking about the logs and state. It seems like it might be fine to track committed logs, but I wonder if runtime files should be ignored. Maybe I should mention propagating commits to the worktree branches since they currently reflect an older commit. The user wanted everything in separate worktrees, but scripts exist only in the main branch. If scripts are needed in worktrees, I could cherry-pick the commits into those branches. Each worktree should ideally be self-contained.\n\n**Evaluating pipeline tracking**\n\nI'm considering that the pipeline would only be tracked in the main branch. Each worktree checkout would have its own version under the relevant branch path, but the root would remain the absolute path from the main workspace. Since the main runtime starts from this workspace, subagents don't need code in their worktree right now. I should check if the config/vault is untracked in branches. If the user wants a proper setup, I need to ensure everything is clear. Also, I'll keep things discreet regarding the group's communications.","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_0b22d22025c20ba70169e9fe545db88191aa006e7b0f5bc5d3\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp6f5nvUkCXIrHbXmDF_hN3JIy0WBAU_Hu1XtK0noaAAQiWUdUPrcoFIrL5G2L0UMaG7KIN4iVvgVzMkh9BcwWhtw8oh1KROtUgbnzheFSD9m5Z1YwT-zh7jLpQsoK1x_kucTc7_5lKZQUz1bF5LzL2uY5j5T94sYII-R_FWm6OGvQ9wqwrTED0MAjJ9bqgCrqxQw732n5Jr1s_vBLQa9en61xGZaMGbUQ2Slb_p7otqwgqGcf19yRaoT5aCQBEDJKw8-4OOxClmexEQmWNF__b5m1sGJsRXx-sa8a88nunD1R1rvScZXMP_7FF5bo1kdfJ1Wmq9kAiWDwO3eP8Zc2MzYankyIjXmJwNqS_BSwscUx-CMd7koLxoJVFkKkQbYk6m5Y6HVss3FbBj4Cpc_MRuSvZv9Qd4na5FBFmeByOPZdKhieoDC8Lkqm7XFdfo1uZm_fWmwf21UFoQP4UyM4C8NZAG66T3kYFXVA8tDR9-VaYdsGJ6E5SAUJVjwDGixq5MHj2vHvw-T99tyYg-u9PDvSMtdBvB6NCOCFoXI_fYEAJT5CHG5gzSFp_9CNkp2fMCUhy9Bs