{"type":"message","id":"f8146e82","parentId":"d9ef05ae","timestamp":"2026-04-23T11:11:57.113Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Done.\n\nWhat’s set up:\n- Worktrees created:\n  - `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/agents/subagent-1` on `subagent-1-branch`\n  - `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/agents/subagent-2` on `subagent-2-branch`\n- Each subagent has:\n  - `config.json`\n  - `logs/`\n  - `task-queue.json`\n  - `vault/goals.md`\n  - `vault/tasks.md`\n  - `vault/memory.md`\n- Shared pipeline created:\n  - `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/pipeline/main_to_subagent_1.json`\n  - `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/pipeline/main_to_subagent_2.json`\n  - `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/pipeline/subagent_1_to_main.json`\n  - `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/pipeline/subagent_2_to_main.json`\n\nRuntime:\n- Main coordinator loop implemented\n- Both subagent loops implemented\n- All three are running in parallel now\n- Verified that both subagents processed seeded tasks and reported back through the pipeline\n\nCode added:\n- `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/agent-system/`\n\nStart command:\n- `bash /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/agent-system/start-all.sh`\n\nCommit:\n- `c438f4d` `Add multi-agent worktree orchestration scaffold`\n\nTiny caveat, because I kept this non-invasive, the orchestration code lives in the main workspace and manages the two worktrees from there. The worktrees themselves are isolated and have their own configs, queues, logs, and vault state.\n\nIf you want, next I can make this cleaner by:\n1. adding stop/restart scripts,\n2. making task assignment CLI-based,\n3. or moving the runtime fully into each worktree branch.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0b22d22025c20ba70169e9fe695f048191ac83ca6874eb5798\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":191,"output":407,"cacheRead":24448,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":25046,"cost":{"input":